{
  "stem": "14387.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we took the train and left.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we did not know that that was the last train ever allowed out of Norway.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That was the last train, that the Germans stopped all trains going-- all trains to cross the border.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "All you could do was get to the border.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we did not know that was the last train, so we just took the last train out.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And after some days-- or actually it was a week, I don't remember exactly, it might have been weeks-- my husband and his brothers realized that there was not going to be any Norwegian army fighting against the Germans.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was no such thing.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So they skied-- they got on skis, and they skied right across Norway to the border.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It took them several days.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But actually, that was a very dangerous thing to do, because the border was patrolled, and when they got close to the border they saw these troops skiing down-- it was the middle of winter.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They saw these troops, and they didn't know if they were Germans or Swedish or-- well, they knew they wouldn't be Norwegian.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they thought, well, if they're Germans, that's the end of us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They'll just shoot them, because they had done that to others.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They just shoot them right there at the border, if they're trying to cross.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But then they saw the Swedish uniforms, and the Swedish soldiers came down and escorted them across the border.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was the Spring of 1940, uh-huh.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "April-- well, it was, yeah, the spring, April of 1940.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, well, with the whole family, there were 21 of us-- we stayed in this old house.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] It was a very old house, it was halfway abandoned.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
